<subSubSection id="A6EBB29F40E8F0C1F35B36186E9FE44D" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="C6AC15A7E3805414463358A609E5EE44" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">
<taxonomicName id="4D57A7FD70ADAC277683B315E6A44927" LSID="DB2B17F1-4503-5DD2-BA47-E8FE69B0E290" authority="Wooton &amp; Standley, Contr. U. S. Natl. Herb. 16: 153. 1913." authorityName="Wooton &amp; Standley, Contr. U. S. Natl. Herb. 16: 153. 1913." class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Onagraceae" genus="Gaura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gaura glandulosa" order="Myrtiflorae" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="glandulosa">
<pageBreakToken id="3394BF8967D5C2559FDC5D6F6E0A791A" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" start="start">Gaura</pageBreakToken>
glandulosa Wooton &amp; Standley, Contr. U.S. Natl. Herb. 16: 153. 1913.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BB2E3CFD06799971B26F891DBB7B7190" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" type="type">
<paragraph id="7EC2818C7A77D31F6FC1E6C426069DBA" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7471C044F7299DB4F8925ED997741BA3" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">United States. New Mexico: Catron County, Reserve, 9 July 1906, E. O. Wootons.n. (Holotype: US 561072!; Isotype: US!).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="09BA86E76F3F9D2AD22B5EE566E414B8" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">
Annual herb from a stout taproot, usually well-branched at the base and above, 15-100 cm tall, villous proximally, the leaves subglabrous to densely short-villous, becoming subglabrous, strigillose and/or glandular puberulent distally. Leaves: rosette leaves lyrate, 3-15 
<normalizedToken id="8F54F2AED496699E134CBAF35831C2A1" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-1 cm; cauline leaves 1-9 
<normalizedToken id="7C1D84F6BBF5603DB8C293AC51836C23" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.1-0.8 cm, linear to very narrowly elliptic or narrowly lanceolate, sinuate-dentate to subentire, subsessile. Flowers 4-merous, opening at sunset; floral tube 6-10 mm; sepals 6-12 mm; petals 5.5-9.5 mm; filaments 4-6 mm, anthers 2-3 mm, pollen 90-100% fertile; style 11-18.5 mm. Capsule indehiscent, 6-8 
<normalizedToken id="08A41DCE9F08A589B25AEEA8EE1A4324" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 mm, nut-like, hard, woody, not reflexed, broadly winged on the angles and deeply furrowed between the angles, the body ellipsoid or narrowly obovoid, narrowed at the base but not stipitate. Seeds 4, 2-3 mm, ovoid, usually flattened on one or several sides by crowding in the fruit, yellowish to reddish brown. Gametic chromosome number: n = 7. Self-compatible.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EFC0792F4C5A692A50BC74064D58E351" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" type="phenology and distribution">
<paragraph id="3B168E5927BEF764A50EBE92A109A8E2" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Phenology and distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="83DA5247AFACA159A756944E5926036F" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Flowering from (May) June to October. In Arizona from eastern Mohave County south through the mountains of central Arizona to eastern Pima County and the southwestern quarter of New Mexico, and in Mexico southward in the Sierra Madre Occidental to eastern Sonora and throughout the western halves of Chihuahua and Durango, often in disturbed sites in or on sandy washes, slopes, grasslands, meadows, pinyon-juniper or ponderosa pine woodlands, and sometimes on volcanic cinders; 760-2750 m.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DBCF130A5368246B9DF3BCABD20B14A9" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">
<taxonomicName id="5AFC0DD8AF3AA17F7D73DB8B4B9E95E4" authorityName="Krakos &amp; W. L. Wagner" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Krakos &amp; W. L. Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="2013" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtiflorae" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="podocarpa">
<emphasis id="B46872DDCE1F3C5C8734F5B46C5B2277" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Oenothera podocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the first species to branch off in the subsect. 
<taxonomicName id="86D1AEF3A3ACA132B43DB8817B402EDA" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Onagraceae" genus="Gaura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtiflorae" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="858CC1EE8CE1454FA514DFB5AB4802AA" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Gaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade (
<figureCitation id="248633BF44BECC8B8C6194583758C74D" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Portion of a Bayesian tree of Oenothera sect. Gaura within a larger analysis of one of two major clades of Oenothera, which has been referred to as clade B by Wagner et al. (2007) with several outgroup species of the other major clade (A) of Oenothera from Krakos et al. (unpubl.). The phylogeny is based on nuclear sequences of ITS and ETS and the chloroplast markers rps 16, ndh F, trn L-F, and rbcl. The labels use the most recent prior taxonomy, placing the group in Oenothera (Wagner et al. 2007), using the taxon delimitations of Raven and Gregory (1972). The taxa involved in the proposed changes here are in bold. Numbers above nodes indicate Bayesian posterior probability values." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10460" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), whereas 
<taxonomicName id="2E4DF72FF52CA0B64642E035072F3BF4" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtiflorae" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="hexandra">
<emphasis id="B71C04B499DAD8748DDB67BA374C8AEB" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Oenothera hexandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is nested well within the subsect. 
<taxonomicName id="1D35D7BAA007ADA613DEF66A4DB2CAE9" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Onagraceae" genus="Gaura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtiflorae" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D24244AD18C2DAE5DA3BE1A1B26C93C7" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Gaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade. The epithet 
<normalizedToken id="B90E1038B7F495A82DB5724EE3079157" originalValue="“podocarpa”">&quot;podocarpa&quot;</normalizedToken>
was selected among the three equally available names at the species rank for this species. Previously, 
<taxonomicName id="A69769343EE91E1F94F37D8EF0EF0F9A" authorityName="Woot &amp; Standl" authorityYear="1913" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Onagraceae" genus="Gaura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtiflorae" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis id="D5CCABE1FBAF838D4F00C6B276760438" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Gaura gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, one of four species published simultaneously by Wooton and Standley,was selected by 
<bibRefCitation id="CB692B3852C526DA1993FEC007A58582" author="Munz, PA" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Torrey Botanical Club" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" pagination="105 - 122" publicationUrl="10.2307/2480964" refId="B6" refString="Munz, PA, 1938. Studies in Onagraceae XI. A revision of the genus Gaura. Bulletin of the Torrey Botanical Club 65: 105 - 122, 10.2307/2480964" title="Studies in Onagraceae XI. A revision of the genus Gaura." url="10.2307/2480964" volume="65" year="1938">Munz (1938)</bibRefCitation>
, while placing the other three into synonymy. 
<bibRefCitation id="117AD23103269D5BF3A8F28FD1F43229" author="Tidestrom, I" journalOrPublisher="Catholic University Press" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" refId="B9" refString="Tidestrom, I, Kittell, T, 1941. A Flora of Arizona and New Mexico. Catholic University Press" title="A Flora of Arizona and New Mexico." year="1941">Tidestrom and Kittell (1941)</bibRefCitation>
apparently unaware of the Munz publication selected 
<taxonomicName id="CF484A28D173556DEEA7C685E67A7909" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Onagraceae" genus="Gaura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtiflorae" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="glandulosa">
<emphasis id="53825527BEAF8AF75AFCF8B4113C2457" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Gaura glandulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but were incorrect as they should have used 
<taxonomicName id="DF79A0482A268774DA76DC82657EBDAD" authorityName="Woot &amp; Standl" authorityYear="1913" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Onagraceae" genus="Gaura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtiflorae" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis id="2E48418A5875E37886788FB93C8E2A62" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Gaura gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They did not establish any new priority.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
